# React Native Patterns

## Styling Rules

1. **Always use StyleSheet.create** - Co-locate in `.styles.ts` files
2. **Never inline styles** - Performance penalty on every render
3. **Platform-specific styles** - Use `Platform.select()`

```typescript
// MyComponent.styles.ts
import { StyleSheet, Platform } from 'react-native';

export const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    padding: 16,
    ...Platform.select({
      ios: { shadowOpacity: 0.1 },
      android: { elevation: 4 },
    }),
  },
});
```

## Accessibility

Add to all interactive elements:
```typescript
<TouchableOpacity
  accessibilityRole="button"
  accessibilityLabel="Submit form"
>
  <Text>Submit</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

## Common Pitfalls

❌ **Never mutate state directly**
```typescript
user.name = 'Jane'; // BAD
setUser(prev => ({ ...prev, name: 'Jane' })); // GOOD
```

❌ **Avoid && for conditional rendering**
```typescript
{count && <Text>{count}</Text>} // Can render 0
{count ? <Text>{count}</Text> : null} // GOOD
```

❌ **No class components**
```typescript
class MyComponent extends Component {} // NEVER
const MyComponent = () => {} // ALWAYS
```
